13. Write a program to read the numbers until -1 is encountered. Find the 
average of positive numbers and negative numbers entered by user. 
Sample Input: 
Enter -1 to exitâ€¦ 
Enter the number: 7 
Enter the number: -2 
Enter the number: 9 
Enter the number: -8 
Enter the number: -6 
Enter the number: -4 
Enter the number: 10 
Enter the number:  -1 
Sample Output: 
The average of negative numbers is: -5.0 
The average of positive numbers is : 8.66666667

CODE: 
public class AverageNumbers {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int posSum = 0, negSum = 0;
        int posCount = 0, negCount = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < args.length; i++) {
            int num = Integer.parseInt(args[i]);

            if (num == -1) {
                break; // stop when -1 is entered
            }

            if (num > 0) {
                posSum += num;
                posCount++;
            } else if (num < 0) {
                negSum += num;
                negCount++;
            }
        }

        if (negCount > 0)
            System.out.println("The average of negative numbers is: " + ((double) negSum / negCount));
        else
            System.out.println("No negative numbers entered.");

        if (posCount > 0)
            System.out.println("The average of positive numbers is: " + ((double) posSum / posCount));
        else
            System.out.println("No positive numbers entered.");
    }
}
